java.util.Collections.singletonList: Returns an immutable list containing only the specified object.
java.util.Optional.empty: Returns an empty Optional instance. No value is present for this Optional.
java.util.Optional.ofNullable: Returns an Optional describing the given value, if non-null, otherwise returns an empty Optional.
java.util.Collections.emptyList: Returns an empty list (immutable). This list is serializable.
java.util.stream.IntStream.range: Returns a sequential ordered IntStream from startInclusive (inclusive) to endExclusive (exclusive) by an incremental step of 1.
java.util.ArrayList.add: Appends the specified element to the end of this list.
